          "vnum": 788,
          "name": "Inside the Rickety House",
          "description": "Stacks of cracked ceramic bowls line the counters and are piled atop a wooden table in the center of the room. Many smaller cylindrical chunks accompany the bowls as well as cover an ancient rug adorning the floor. Pungent, dried herbs hang from the walls and ceiling. Fitted into the eastern wall is a dirty and useless window.",
